<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3831] build of test/cpp/src/TestClient.cpp fails with newer gcc on platforms with unsigned char due to narrowing conversions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3831</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Specifically, we get a bunch of errors like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            test/cpp/src/TestClient.cpp:404:15: error: narrowing conversion of &apos;-1&apos; from &apos;int&apos; to &apos;char&apos; inside { } &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-Wnarrowing&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;gcc faq talks about this: &lt;a href=&quot;https://gcc.gnu.org/wiki/FAQ#Wnarrowing&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gcc.gnu.org/wiki/FAQ#Wnarrowing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve only seen this in gcc-6, but the faq seems to indicate it could occur in gcc-5 as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
